quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  19,85,"On the Day We will gather the righteous to the Most Merciful as a delegation"
  19,86,"And will drive the criminals to Hell in thirst"
  19,87,"None will have [power of] intercession except he who had taken from the Most Merciful a covenant.{1}",footnotes:1:[Not to worship other than Him.]
  20,67,"And he sensed within himself apprehension, did Moses."
  20,68,"We [i.e., Allāh] said, "
  20,69,"And throw what is in your right hand; it will swallow up what they have crafted. What they have crafted is but the trick of a magician, and the magician will not succeed wherever he is."
  21,43,"Or do they have gods to defend them other than Us? They are unable [even] to help themselves, nor can they be protected from Us."
  21,44,"But, [on the contrary], We have provided good things for these [disbelievers] and their fathers until life was prolonged for them. Then do they not see that We set upon the land, reducing it from its borders?{1} Is it they who will overcome?",footnotes:1:[See footnote to 13:41.]
  21,45,"Say, "
  22,19,"These{1} are two adversaries who have disputed over their Lord. But those who disbelieved will have cut out for them garments of fire. Poured upon their heads will be scalding water",footnotes:1:[i.e., the believers and the disbelievers.]
  22,20,"By which is melted that within their bellies and [their] skins."
  22,21,"And for [striking] them are maces of iron."